The numbers are placed on a hexagonal grid in a spiral.
For a hexagonal spiral the maximal number in the \(d\)-th ring (distance
\(d\) from the centre) is  

\[
N_{\max }(d)=1+3d(d+1)
\]

and the first number of that ring is  

\[
N_{\text{start}}(d)=N_{\max }(d-1)+1=2+3(d-1)d .
\]

The six directions we use (going counter‑clockwise) are  

\[
D_0=(0,-1),\; D_1=(-1,0),\; D_2=(-1,1),\;
D_3=(0,1),\; D_4=(1,0),\; D_5=(1,-1).
\]

Starting a ring at \((d,0)\) (which holds \(N_{\text{start}}(d)\)),
moving \(k\) steps around the ring gives the coordinate  

\[
(d,0)+\sum_{i=0}^{s-1} dD_i+tD_s,
\qquad\text{where }k=s\,d+t,\;0\le s\le5,\;0\le t<d.
\]

---

### 1.  Locate 2026

\(2026\) lies in ring \(d=26\) because  

\[
N_{\max }(25)=1951<2026\le N_{\max }(26)=2107 .
\]

The first number of this ring is \(N_{\text{start}}(26)=1952\);
the offset of 2026 is \(2026-1952=74\).

\(74 = 2\cdot 26 + 22\), so we are on side \(s=2\) after \(t=22\) steps.
Using the direction list above we obtain the axial coordinate  

\[
(26,0)+26\,(0,-1)+26\,(-1,0)+22\,(-1,1)=(-22,-4).
\]

Thus \(2026\) is at \((-22,-4)\).

---

### 2.  The six neighbours

Add the six direction vectors to \((-22,-4)\):

\[
\begin{aligned}
(-22,-5),\;(-23,-4),\;(-23,-3),\;(-22,-3),\;(-21,-4),\;(-21,-5).
\end{aligned}
\]

For each neighbour we find its ring \(d'\), then its offset in that
ring, and finally its number.

| neighbour (axial) | \(d'\) | side | \(t\) | offset | number |
|-------------------|-------|------|------|--------|--------|
| \((-22,-5)\) | 27 | side 2 | 22 | \(2\cdot27+22=76\) | \(2108+76=2184\) |
| \((-23,-4)\) | 27 | side 2 | 23 | \(2\cdot27+23=77\) | \(2108+77=2185\) |
| \((-23,-3)\) | 26 | side 2 | 23 | \(2\cdot26+23=75\) | \(1952+75=2027\) |
| \((-22,-3)\) | 25 | side 2 | 22 | \(2\cdot25+22=72\) | \(1802+72=1874\) |
| \((-21,-4)\) | 25 | side 2 | 21 | \(2\cdot25+21=71\) | \(1802+71=1873\) |
| \((-21,-5)\) | 26 | side 2 | 21 | \(2\cdot26+21=73\) | \(1952+73=2025\) |

---

### 3.  Sum of the neighbours

\[
\begin{aligned}
S &= 2184+2185+2027+1874+1873+2025\\
  &= 12168 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{12168}
\]
